Version 0.3.23, 2026-04-30
Changes and bugfixes:
- Frontend/admin modernization closure: phases 1-7 are complete for the compatibility scope; remaining items are explicitly future/non-goals (framework reskin, route-specific visual redesign, in-app CSP header enforcement, and unproven selector deletion).
- CSS token closure: shipped themes now expose `cellmenu*` variables alongside existing shell/title/list/menu tokens, and dynamic parser FTP-password panels use shared CSS classes/tokens instead of inline JS `style.cssText`.
- Embedded parser confirmation UI coverage: a mocked-`EventSource` Playwright smoke test now emits `confirm_action`, verifies the visible Yes/No panel, and confirms Yes starts a new EventSource with the nonce-backed `confirmUrl` without executing destructive actions.
- Admin message hardening: login, upgrade, parser, servers, users, players, string editor, and FTP builder error messages are escaped before template output where applicable and use the established alert/live-region pattern.
- Admin FTP builder robustness: invalid server ids now render a normal escaped alert instead of relying on a broken row check; id loading uses a bound query while preserving field names and popup behavior.
- Responsive layout containment: narrow public/admin viewports now stack the 400px header logo and selector controls; long public/admin menus, public pagers, dense admin list tables, representative public content/list tables, and player/round detail shells scroll inside their own strips instead of forcing page-level horizontal overflow. Admin summary/config/filter panels and public search/error panels now fit the mobile body chrome.
- Admin server editor usability: add/edit server form fields now have stable labels/IDs plus HTML5 hints that mirror existing server-side rules (`required` name/IP/port/log path and numeric port bounds) while preserving all field names and POST behavior.
- Admin user editor usability: add/edit user form fields now have stable labels/IDs, username autocomplete/required hint, and password autocomplete hints; password fields stay optional in the shared edit form so existing password-change behavior is unchanged.
- Admin string editor usability: filter and string ID inputs now use standard text inputs; add/edit string form keeps stable labels/IDs and adds the required/autocomplete-off hint for the string ID while preserving language/text field names.
- Admin server save validation: relative game-log paths such as `gamelogs/cod4_normal.log` are validated relative to the UltraStats app root, matching parser behavior; uncreatable paths now report the existing validation error instead of throwing a PHP 8 `fclose(false)` fatal.
- Admin server editor messaging: server validation errors are escaped before template output and the error box now uses alert live-region semantics like the other hardened admin forms.
- Parser confirmation coverage: Playwright now asserts classic parser destructive confirmations and embedded parser SSE confirmation payloads expose nonce-backed Yes URLs for delete server, delete stats, and reset last log line, with no legacy `verify=yes` links.
- Admin parser errors: parser wrapper validation messages are escaped before template output, and the missing-server path now reports the requested ID instead of referencing an undefined variable.
- JavaScript IE cleanup: removed active MSIE/Trident-era branches from `common.js` (`window.event` / `cancelBubble` fallbacks, string-based `setTimeout`, and the Trident-only menu tooltip path). The old `HoverPopupMenuHelp` global remains as a no-op shim while modern menu usability relies on CSS flyouts/native titles.
- Admin index CSP cleanup: medal group toggles and medal autosave/recalculate logic now run from shared `common.js` using existing checkbox classes plus `#medal-autorecalc-status` data attributes; `admin/index.html` no longer embeds inline scripts.
- Embedded parser CSP cleanup: the admin `parser.html` EventSource UI now runs from shared `common.js` instead of an inline `<script>` block, preserving SSE event names, cancel flow, resume/run-totals chaining, and dynamic confirm/FTP panels.
- Classic parser CSP cleanup: parser-core HTML now loads shared `common.js`; parser autoscroll and resume/run-total auto-reload behavior use `data-parser-autoscroll` / `data-reload-*` markers instead of inline `<script>` blocks.
- FTP builder CSP cleanup: popup centering/focus and saved auto-close now use `common.js` handlers with `data-popup-center-*` / `data-ftpbuilder-close-delay` markers; `servers-ftpbuilder.html` no longer embeds inline scripts.
- Template CSP cleanup: remaining active template event-handler attributes were removed from shared popup panels, public weapon/damage stat bars, and admin server action tooltips; delegated `.us-popup-help` / `.us-popup-panel` handlers in `common.js` preserve hover popups while `rg` reports no `onclick`/`onkeyup`/mouse-hover attributes in templates.
- Player detail CSP cleanup: hit-location body-map and killed-by legend hovers in `players-detail.html` now use delegated `common.js` handlers with `data-*` attributes; the repeated inline mouse handlers and page-local `HoverPlayerImage` script were removed while preserving popup/legend behavior.
- Public menu CSP cleanup: shared top-menu toggle, timeout-extension, and popup-help behavior moved from inline event attributes in `include_menu.html` to delegated `common.js` handlers backed by `data-*` attributes; smoke asserts the menu has no inline JavaScript handlers and still toggles.
- Admin navigation polish: confirmation/error back links in users, players, string editor, upgrade, and parser confirm views now use real fallback URLs plus delegated `.us-history-back` behavior instead of `href="javascript:history.back();"`.
- Homepage top players: Played Time column now stays on one line by scoping a no-wrap/min-width rule to the main top-player table, preventing day/time values from wrapping in the dark theme at narrow widths.
- Phase 6 admin UX pilot: destructive parser actions (`delete`, `deletestats`, `resetlastlogline` on browser/SSE paths) now require a single-use `parser_confirm_nonce` in the confirming URL instead of `verify=yes` alone; reduces CSRF exposure while keeping EventSource GET-compatible resume. CLI/cron `parser-shell.php` remains unchanged (RUNMODE_COMMANDLINE).
- User admin: confirmed account deletes use POST + session CSRF (`ultrastats_csrf`, `UltraStats_AdminCsrf*` in `functions_common.php`) plus `RedirectResult` PRG; token is regenerated on successful login (`CheckUserLogin`). Intermediate template `admin_securecheck.html` POSTs clean body fields; alert cell uses `PriorityError` alignment.
- Embedded parser SSE: destructive confirm banner classes `us-parser-confirm-*` and `:root` tokens in `defaults.css` (`--us-parser-confirm-*`) replace hard-coded inline banner colours (Phase 6.2 / 4.2 incremental).
- New language strings `LN_WARNINGRESETLASTLOGLINE` (en/de) for reset-last-log-line confirmation.
- Documentation: `docs/admin-destructive-actions-inventory.md`, `docs/admin-phase6-manual-confirm-checklist.md`; `SECURITY.md` CSRF/nonces; roadmap progress (Phase 6 partial, Phase 4.4 gated on screenshot baselines); `docs/template-variable-trust.md` rows for touched routes.
- Tests: Playwright asserts POST user delete without valid CSRF is rejected; fixes admin players verify back-link href selector (`javascript:history.back()`).
- Admin players / string editor: delete confirmation uses POST + session CSRF (`ultrastats_csrf`, `admin_confirm_player_delete` / `admin_confirm_string_delete`); `verify=yes` no longer executes deletes on those routes. `SECURITY.md` + destructive-actions inventory updated; smoke asserts confirm forms and CSRF rejection for players + stringeditor.
- Phase 1.5: `e2e/tests/admin-visual-baseline.spec.ts` — full-page admin index screenshot size guard after login; optional golden `toHaveScreenshot` when `ULTRASTATS_ADMIN_VISUAL_BASELINE=1`.
- Admin templates: `admin/players.html`, `admin/users.html`, `admin/stringeditor.html` error strips use `ErrorMsg` + `role="alert"` / `aria-live`; `UltraStats_h` on `ERROR_MSG` before output in the matching PHP scripts.
- CSS: `defaults.css` adds `--us-parser-debug-grid-bg`, `--us-priority-emergency-*`; `.us-parser-debug-grid` / `.PriorityEmergency` consume them; admin players list filter row uses `.us-admin-player-filter-bar` flex toolbar.
- Admin slim header loads `js/common.js` with `defer`; FTP builder saved popup close uses `us-admin-ftpbuilder-close` + `UltraStatsAdminCloseFtpBuilderPopup` (delegated click) instead of inline `onclick`.
- Admin UX polish: optional browser confirms (`.us-confirm-nav`) for GET-first destructive entry links (users/players/stringeditor + parser delete/deletestats/resetlastlogline in parser/servers views); declining the prompt keeps the page unchanged, accepting proceeds to existing server-side confirm/nonce flow.
- Admin servers edit: FTP builder launch button now uses delegated popup metadata (`.us-open-popup`, `data-popup-*`) instead of inline `onclick="NewWindow(...)"`.
- Phase 3.3 completion pass: remaining template inline `style="..."` attributes were moved to shared utility classes in `defaults.css`; parser classic debug shell body color now uses `.us-parser-body`; player name color rendering no longer outputs `<font>` (uses `<span>`).
- Phase 4.2 completion (all shipped themes): remaining hardcoded theme/default color literals were tokenized into `:root` variables in `src/css/defaults.css` and `src/themes/{default,dark,codww}/main.css`; debug/status color blocks consume tokens.
- Phase 4.3 completion (inner layout only): parser embed toolbar/status/cancel layout now uses reusable classes (`us-parser-embed-toolbar`, `us-parser-stream-status`, `us-parser-cancel-btn`, `us-hidden`) and utility layout classes are reused across admin/public inner blocks; outer table chrome remains unchanged (4.4 still deferred).
- Phase 4.4 completion (aggressive): outer chrome shell modernized via shared templates (`include_header`/`include_footer`, `admin_header`/`admin_footer`) by adding `us-chrome-top`, `us-chrome-body`, and `us-chrome-footer`; `defaults.css` now provides responsive shell sizing/radius/shadow tokens and themes override `--us-chrome-*` as needed.
- Tests: Playwright smoke now asserts `us-chrome-*` shell presence on representative public/admin routes; visual baseline spec includes public index outer chrome screenshot gate (strict `toHaveScreenshot` when `ULTRASTATS_ADMIN_VISUAL_BASELINE=1`).
- Screenshot matrix (public + admin): added `e2e/tests/full-route-visual.spec.ts` to capture full-page artifacts for list and detail routes (including `info-maps.php?id=mp_strike&serverid=2`) with optional strict screenshot compare behind `ULTRASTATS_ADMIN_VISUAL_BASELINE=1`.
- CSS fixes from artifact pass: `info-maps.html` now uses responsive two-column layout classes (`us-map-detail-layout`, `us-map-detail-col`) and `defaults.css` stacks these columns on narrow widths; `us-chrome-top/body/footer` now use `overflow: visible` to prevent clipping in screenshoted pages.
- Mobile/narrow viewport sweep (1280/1024/900): captured full public/admin screenshot + shell-metrics matrix and triaged shared-shell issues first (top/menu/pager/body/footer alignment stayed consistent across sampled routes).
- Mobile overflow hardening: for narrow screens (`max-width: 1100px`), `defaults.css` sets `.us-chrome-body` as a bounded block-level shell with horizontal overflow containment so dense legacy tables (e.g., `index.php`, `players.php`) scroll inside body chrome instead of causing page-level horizontal overflow.
- Verification: re-ran the 1280/1024/900 matrix after the CSS change and executed focused Playwright smoke subset (`core public routes render without server errors`, `critical admin screens still load with legacy routes`) to confirm route-level compatibility.
- Phase 1 completion: baseline track is now fully closed (`1.1`–`1.5`) — deeper core smoke route assertions for public/admin shell contracts, mandatory HTML validation suite (`e2e/tests/html-validation.spec.ts`), completed `docs/template-variable-trust.md` closure matrix, and strict visual baseline assertions enabled by default (no `ULTRASTATS_ADMIN_VISUAL_BASELINE` gate in baseline specs).
- Visual baseline snapshots: committed first strict snapshot set under `e2e/tests/admin-visual-baseline.spec.ts-snapshots/` and `e2e/tests/full-route-visual.spec.ts-snapshots/` (generated with `--update-snapshots` on win32/chromium).
- userchange.php: fixed HTTP redirect after language/style/time-filter dropdowns when UltraStats is installed under a URL subfolder (relative Location no longer doubles the path segment, which caused 404; same-host referer matching now tolerates a port in HTTP_REFERER vs HTTP_HOST).
- Admin database upgrade: database_installedversion is written only when every upgrade SQL statement succeeds; on failure the version is left unchanged and the UI tells the operator to fix errors and retry.
- CI/tests: GitHub Actions PHP CI (php -l on src, PHPUnit for DB helpers and gamelog fixture); Composer dev dependencies for PHPUnit (composer.json; vendor/ gitignored).
- Security: admin result.php now sanitizes the meta refresh target with UltraStats_SanitizeRedirectTarget, HTML-escapes the flash message and redirect href in the language string, and caps the refresh interval; blocks javascript:/data: and quote/control injection in redirect targets (UltraStats_SanitizeRedirectTarget extended).
- Templates: fixed javascript:history.back() typo on admin players list and parser helper back link.
- Security: DieWithErrorMsg / DieWithFriendlyErrorMsg now escape error detail text before rendering in HTML (line breaks preserved); common.js popup title/content now uses textContent instead of innerHTML.
- Tests: PHPUnit coverage for UltraStats_SanitizeRedirectTarget and UltraStats_EscapeErrorTextForHtml; Playwright admin result.php redirect/message cases.
- Templates / HTML shell: HTML5 doctype (`<!DOCTYPE html>`), `<meta charset="utf-8">`, and viewport meta on public `include_header`, admin `admin_header`, install wizard, slim admin header, rounds chatlog iframe page, and parser `CreateHTMLHeader()` wrapper.
- Tests: Playwright asserts HTML5 doctype and charset meta on representative routes.
- DieWithErrorMsg / DieWithFriendlyErrorMsg now emit a minimal HTML5 document (DOCTYPE, charset, viewport) via UltraStats_RenderStandaloneErrorDocumentHtml; table markup unchanged.
- Templates: removed legacy IE6 PNG alpha hacks (AlphaImageLoader filters and CheckAlphaPNGImage scripts) from install header, index medal tiles, and medals detail; removed unused CheckAlphaPNGImage from common.js.
- Tests: PHPUnit asserts standalone error HTML shell.
- Presentational cleanup: parser user-check and FTP password forms (functions_parser-helpers) use us-error-text with HTML-escaped labels; admin servers FTP builder verify output uses the same class and escapes IP, port, path, and user in error lines.
- Templates / CSS: last played rounds tables (players-detail, info-maps, info-gametypes, serverstats) stack date/time and Details link in one column; separate columns for gametype and map; `.us-lastrounds-*` layout rules in defaults.css (fixes cramped middle column).
- Templates: homepage index and rounds list use `<span class="WinnerTeam|LoserTeam|DrawTeam">` instead of `<font class="…">` for team colours; DM winner column stray `</font>` closures removed; rounds.html map-thumb cell `&nbsp` corrected to `&nbsp;`.
- players-detail.php: hit-location hover damage text uses `<span class="us-damage-pct">` with validated CSS hex colours instead of `<font color>`; helpers UltraStats_PlayerDetailCssHexColor / UltraStats_PlayerDetailHoverDamagePctHtml; `.us-damage-pct-zero` in defaults.css for 0% yellow.
- Documentation: docs/template-variable-trust.md — starter `{VAR}` trust-level note (Phase 1.4 / 7.2).
- Front-end JS (Phase 5.2): public `include_header.html` server/language/style and `include_pager.html` time-filter year/month `<select>` elements use class `us-autosubmit-select`; `common.js` submits the parent `<form>` on `change` (replaces inline `OnChange="document.*form.submit()"`).
- Public header (a11y / Track B): `include_header.html` — server, language, and style dropdowns have stable `id` attributes and their row labels use `<label for="…">` (same form field names and `userchange.php` flow).
- Install wizard (Phase 3.3): step 2 file/dir permission status column uses CSS classes `us-install-perm-ok` / `us-install-perm-fail` in `defaults.css` instead of `td bgcolor` (colours unchanged: #007700 / #770000).
- Templates / CSS: public top menu (`include_menu.html`) — table class `us-top-menu`; `defaults.css` sets `table-layout: auto` and `td.topmenu1 { width: auto }` so long translated labels are no longer clipped by legacy narrow `td width` attributes (visible under HTML5 / strict layout).
- Templates / CSS: players-detail Trefferzonen — `table.us-hitloc-inner` uses `table-layout: auto`; `.us-hitloc-chart` gives the 220px-wide sprite column full width (`content-box` + `width: 220px`); nested sprite `table` has class `us-hitloc-figure` with `border-spacing: 0`, `td { padding: 0 }`, `img { display: block }` (removes inline baseline gaps). Fixes misaligned body-part slices caused by the earlier `fixed` layout / squeezed chart column.
- Templates: `damagetypes.html` and `weapons.html` (weapon/damage type list rows) — add missing `</td>` after the player-count summary bar so list rows are valid table markup (avoids browser-dependent column drift next to the external-info cell on weapons).
- Templates: public `include_header.html` / `include_pager.html` and admin `index.html` / `stringeditor.html` — `STYLE="…"` on `<select>` elements normalized to lowercase `style="…"` (HTML5 attribute style).
- Templates / strings: legacy uppercase anchors (`<A HREF="…">` / `</A>`) normalized to `<a href="…">` / `</a>` in HTML templates, installer language strings (`LN_INSTALL_ERRORINSTALLED` en/de), and parser confirmation HTML (`functions_parser-helpers.php`; URLs unchanged).
- Templates / strings: legacy uppercase bold and line breaks (`<B>` / `<BR>`) normalized to `<b>` / `<br>` in HTML templates, installer strings (`LN_INSTALL_*` bold snippets en/de), and admin `result.html` (appearance unchanged).
- Parser: `functions_parser.php` — resume / time-limit notice HTML uses `<b>`, `</a>`, `</b>` (was mixed `</A>` / `<B>` in printed parser messages).
- Templates: italic markup `<I>` / `</I>` → `<i>` / `</i>` on pager / helper rows; fixed malformed attribute glue `width="100%"class="…"` → `width="100%" class="…"` (players, rounds, weapons, damagetypes, medals, serverstats, admin players/stringeditor).
- Templates: legacy event attributes normalized to HTML5 lowercase (`OnMouseOver` / `OnMouseMove` / `OnMouseOut` / `OnClick` → `onmouseover` / `onmousemove` / `onmouseout` / `onclick`) where used (menu, header help icon, players-detail hovers, stats bars, admin servers / FTP builder).
- Templates / parser shell: `<body>` IE-era margin attributes lowercased (`topmargin` / `leftmargin` / `marginwidth` / `marginheight`) on public/admin/install/chatlog headers; `functions_parser-helpers.php` parser wrapper uses lowercase body margins, `<script>` / `</script>`, and `onload` (was `TOPMARGIN` / `SCRIPT` / `OnLoad`).
- Templates / PHP shell: redundant `type="text/css"` removed from `<link rel="stylesheet">` tags (HTML5 default); standalone error document helper in `functions_common.php` and parser CSS links in `functions_parser-helpers.php` updated the same way.
- Templates: redundant `type` on `<script>` removed (`type='text/javascript'` on `common.js` in public/admin/install headers; inline blocks in `admin/index.html` use bare `<script>`).
- Templates: `admin/servers-ftpbuilder.html` — obsolete `language="javascript"` removed from `<script>` (HTML5 default).
- Templates: replace legacy `document.all` with `document.getElementById` (FTP URL preview; commented axis player-legend block in `players-detail.html` for consistency with modern browsers).
- Templates: fixed malformed `<td>` markup (`colspan="2"class="…"` missing space before `class`) on `players-detail.html` (played-time row) and `rounds.html` (details header cell) — HTML5 parsers treated the cell as invalid and broke the stats table layout (empty value columns, stray ratio bar).
- Front-end JS (Phase 5.1 / 5.3): `common.js` — removed MSIE/Opera user-agent sniffing; popup positioning uses shared pointer helpers (`UltraStatsPointerPageY` / `UltraStatsPointerClientX`); `disableEventPropagation` uses `stopPropagation`; safe null-checks on `#popupdetails`; public APIs mirrored on `window.UltraStatsUI` for tooling without dropping legacy global names used by templates.
- players-detail.php: hit-location hover HTML (`UltraStats_PlayerDetailHoverDamagePctHtml` and 0% spans) now uses **single-quoted** `class`/`style` attributes so strings do not contain raw `"` — the fragment is embedded in template `OnMouseOver="..."` and double quotes previously terminated the attribute and dumped JS/markup as visible page text.
- Templates / CSS: `players-detail.html` hit-zone blocks (`us-hitloc-*`) add horizontal gutter between the two 50% panels, fixed-width chart column + spacing before the stats table, and `defaults.css` `table-layout: fixed` + column classes so zone names and kill counts are not separated by a wide empty middle column.
Changes (maintainability / SQL):
- CSS (Phase 4.1): `defaults.css` — `:root` custom properties (`--us-color-error`, `--us-color-bar-positive`, etc.); `.ErrorMsg` and `us-error-text` / `us-stat-bar-*` / `us-install-perm-*` / `us-credit-nick` / `us-damage-pct-zero` use `var()` (same effective colours; themes can override on `:root` if needed).
- CSS (Phase 4.1a): `themes/default/main.css`, `themes/dark/main.css`, `themes/codww/main.css` — `:root` tokens (`--us-default-*`, `--us-dark-*`, `--us-codww-*`) for top menu / flyouts; `.topmenu1` / `.topmenu2` / `.topmenu3` and link rules use `var()` (appearance unchanged).
- Parser shell: server list SELECT uses DB_QueryBound (no placeholders).
- info-maps.php / info-gametypes.php: bound parameters for map/gametype keys from ?id= in detail and last-rounds queries.
- Templates (Phase 3.5): public error/update strips are inline in each route template (`index`, `players`, `rounds`, `find-*`, `rounds-detail`, `weapons`, `damagetypes`, `players-detail`, `info-*`, `medals`, `serverstats`); `include_header` inlines `error_installfilereminder`; `admin_header` inlines `isupdateavailable`; `servers.html` / `servers-ftpbuilder.html` inline admin error and FTP-warning markup. PHP still sets `ERROR_DETAILS` / `ERROR_MSG` as before.
- CSS: public top menu (`table.us-top-menu` in `include_menu.html` only) — `td.topmenu1` / `td.topmenu1begin` now use `min-width: max-content` so long translated labels are not squeezed under the next cell (overlap); wide menus scroll horizontally if needed. Admin `admin_menu.html` is unchanged (no `us-top-menu`).
- German UI: `lang/de/main.php` — `LN_GLOBAL_STATS` restored to **präsentiert** (UTF-8); the previous character between “pr” and “sentiert” had been corrupted to U+FFFD.
- Documentation: `docs/template-variable-trust.md` — `{ERROR_DETAILS}` / `{ERROR_MSG}` trust notes; error/update banner markup is inlined in route templates (Phase 7.2).
- CSS (Phase 4.2): structural rules consolidated — `TD` font family/size, `img` border reset, legacy `font` tag rules in `defaults.css`; themes override `TD` text colour only; `rounds-chatlog.html` and `UltraStats_RenderStandaloneErrorDocumentHtml` link `defaults.css` before theme CSS.
- CSS (Phase 4.2b): `defaults.css` — shared layout for `.title` / `.titleSecond` (font, height, text alignment, `background-repeat`) and `font-size` for `.line0`–`.line2` / `.tableBackground`; `themes/{default,dark,codww}/main.css` keep text/background colours, `a.title` link styles, row hovers, and `images/bg_3.png` / `bg_4.png` (visual parity).
- PHP (Phase 7.2a): `functions_common.php` — `UltraStats_h()` wraps `htmlspecialchars(..., ENT_QUOTES, 'UTF-8')`; used by `admin/result.php` (flash `msg` / redirect display), `UltraStats_EscapeErrorTextForHtml`, `UltraStats_RenderStandaloneErrorDocumentHtml`, and the PHP 7.4+ version check message. PHPUnit: `RedirectSanitizeTest::testUltraStats_h_escapesForHtml`.
- Documentation: `docs/template-variable-trust.md` — documents `UltraStats_h()` in helpers and escaping cookbook.
- Front-end JS (Phase 5.1): `common.js` — section banners (pointer helpers, `NewWindow`, toggle display, `#popupdetails`, autosubmit `<select>`, `UltraStatsUI`); ASCII comments replace mojibake in `NewWindow` / `HoverPopupMenuHelp` / Phase 5.2 IIFE block (no runtime change).
- Tests: Playwright — `players.php` and `rounds.php` each assert a visible `td.title` when the list is enabled; `test.skip` if the title row is absent (stats off or empty install).
- Documentation: `docs/template-variable-trust.md` — **Key routes (Phase 1.4)** table (includes weapons, damagetypes, serverstats, medals, about); **Escaping cookbook (Phase 7.2)**.
- Tests: Playwright — `weapons.php`, `damagetypes.php`, `serverstats.php`, `medals.php` assert a visible `td.title` when the feature is on (`test.skip` if absent); `about.php` asserts `td.title` unconditionally.
- Templates: obsolete `<center>` replaced by `<div class="us-center">` with `.us-center { text-align: center; }` in `defaults.css` (public/admin templates; parser and install-hint PHP fragments updated to match).
